-- Bahrain's Investcorp says to acquire U.S.-based Totes Isotoner Corp
-- By David French
-- Tue Apr 22, 2014 02:37AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, April 22 (Reuters) - Bahrain-based alternative investment fund Investcorp <INVB.BH> said on Tuesday it had agreed to acquire U.S.-based accessories brand Totes Isotoner Corp [TOTES.UL] in partnership with private equity firm Freeman Spogli & Co.

No terms were disclosed for the purchase from MidOcean Partners and Bruckmann, Rosser, Sherrill & Co. Investcorp's president for Gulf business, Mohammed al-Shroogi, said the investment would help Totes Isotoner expand both its geographical footprint and its product range.